        {
          "slippage_situation": null
        }
      ],
      "phase_evolution": "During annealing at 950 °C, austenite partially transforms to ferrite, Cr7C3, and intergranular κ-carbides. Above 950 °C, ferrite transforms back to austenite, and carbides dissolve; at 1000 °C, complete recrystallization and dissolution of detrimental carbides, while high Mn/Al/C in austenite leads to fine κ-carbide reprecipitation during water quenching."
    }
