  "unmapped_findings": [
    "The specific ultimate tensile strength (SUTS) of DP1000-5 is 196.5±2.4 MPa·g^{-1}·cm^{3} and the product of SUTS and total elongation exceeds 8 GPa·g^{-1}·cm^{3}·%.",
    "SYS (specific yield strength) of DP1000-5 is 162.7±0.8 MPa·g^{-1}·cm^{3}.",
    "The previous record SUTS (169.9 MPa·g^{-1}·cm^{3}) was held by a 29.05Mn-12.01Al-1.48C-5.13Cr austenitic steel with TE 43.8% and density 6.34 g·cm^{-3}.",
    "β-Mn phase was detected at 700-900 °C, known to be hard and cause brittle fracture when located at grain boundaries.",
    "κ-carbide precipitation at 950-1000 °C consumes Mn/Al/C, leading to reduced austenite lattice parameter and XRD peak shift to higher 2θ.",
    "Granular α ferrite grains pin austenite grain boundaries during annealing, retarding grain growth.",
    "In DP1000-5-TD, δ/γ interfaces are perpendicular to tensile direction, causing additional crack initiation at these interfaces and lower ductility.",
    "Duplex microstructural design with ferrite in two morphologies and nanosized κ-carbide precipitation enables strength-ductility-density synergy beyond existing lightweight steels."
  ]
}